\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Multi-expiration parametric calibration diagnostics (NVDA, 2 to 46 DTE). \textbf  {(a)}~IV smile curves at each of six expirations (2, 4, 7, 14, 25, 46~DTE). Market observations (markers) and model predictions (lines) are colored by DTE; 0~DTE data (diamonds) were excluded from the fit due to gamma compression. The skew flattened with increasing maturity, consistent with $\beta _3 > 0$. \textbf  {(b)}~IV residuals (model $-$ market) by moneyness, colored by DTE. Most residuals fell within $\pm 2$\% IV, with no systematic bias across the moneyness range. \textbf  {(c)}~Model-predicted IV surface as a function of moneyness and DTE (log-scaled). White contour lines mark 35\%, 45\%, and 55\% IV levels; white circles indicate market observations used for calibration. The overall RMSE was 1.15\% IV across the 2 to 46 DTE range.}}{15}{figure.caption.17}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:supp_term_structure}{{6}{15}{Multi-expiration parametric calibration diagnostics (NVDA, 2 to 46 DTE). \textbf {(a)}~IV smile curves at each of six expirations (2, 4, 7, 14, 25, 46~DTE). Market observations (markers) and model predictions (lines) are colored by DTE; 0~DTE data (diamonds) were excluded from the fit due to gamma compression. The skew flattened with increasing maturity, consistent with $\beta _3 > 0$. \textbf {(b)}~IV residuals (model $-$ market) by moneyness, colored by DTE. Most residuals fell within $\pm 2$\% IV, with no systematic bias across the moneyness range. \textbf {(c)}~Model-predicted IV surface as a function of moneyness and DTE (log-scaled). White contour lines mark 35\%, 45\%, and 55\% IV levels; white circles indicate market observations used for calibration. The overall RMSE was 1.15\% IV across the 2 to 46 DTE range}{figure.caption.17}{}}
